  "prompt": "Why do people on the game show \"Wheel of Fortune\" solve the puzzle instead of calling out the letters and getting more money?",
  "response": "People on \"Wheel of Fortune\" often solve the puzzle early for several strategic reasons:\n\n1. Risk management: Solving the puzzle quickly eliminates the risk of losing money by landing on Bankrupt or losing a turn.\n\n2. Accumulated winnings: The money they've already earned remains safe when they solve the puzzle.\n\n3. Bonus Round opportunity: Solving puzzles quickly increases their chances of reaching the bonus round, where they can win additional prizes.\n\n4. Momentum: Successfully solving puzzles can build confidence and create positive momentum during the game.\n\n5. Strategy: Sometimes, solving early prevents opponents from potentially gaining more money if they were to spin and guess letters.\n\nWhile calling out individual letters can potentially earn more money, the overall game strategy often favors solving the puzzle as soon as a contestant feels confident they know the answer.",
